# ─── Agent (AI Assistant) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — OPTIONAL env-var fallback for local dev / single-tenant
# self-hosting. In production (Vercel), DO NOT rely on this — paste the key
# in the in-app Settings → API Keys panel after the first sign-in. The
# framework stores it encrypted in `app_secrets` (see
# apps/staff-web/server/register-secrets.ts) and resolves it per-user without
# any deploy-level env-var dependency.
#
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─── Auth allowlist (P1b.1-02) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# CUSTOMER_ALLOWED_EMAILS — comma-separated emails allowed to sign in to /gymos.
# Empty or unset = dev fallback (no allowlist enforcement). Pilot-only gate,
# replaced by org-based ACL in P1a.
CUSTOMER_ALLOWED_EMAILS=

# ─── WhatsApp Cloud API (production env vars) ────────────────────────────────
# These are read directly by:
#   - apps/staff-web/app/routes/webhooks.whatsapp.tsx (process.env)
#   - services/worker/src/lib/env.ts (Zod-validated)
#   - services/edge-webhooks/src/lib/env.ts (Zod-validated)
# Set them via `vercel env add` for staff-web and `fly secrets set` for the
# Fly services. The in-app Settings → API Keys panel surfaces these for
# rotation/visibility but the handlers above do NOT read from app_secrets yet.
# WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
# WHATSAPP_APP_SECRET=
# WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=
# WHATSAPP_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=  # optional — worker template-sync only
